Aloha President Kouchi, Speaker Nakamura, and Members of the Legislature:
This is to inform you that on June 26, 2026, the following bill was signed into law:
H.B. NO. 1800, H.D. 1, S.D. 1, RELATING TO THE STATE BUDGET.
CD. 1 ACT 175
Mahalo,
Josh Green, M.D.
Governor, State of Hawaii

Approved by the Governor
ACT 175
JUN 2 6 2026
HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
H.B. NO.
THIRTY-THIRD LEGISLATURE, 2026
STATE OF HAWAII
C.D. 1
A BILL FOR AN ACT
RELATING TO THE STATE BUDGET.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAII:
1 SECTION 1. This Act shall be known and may be cited as the
2 Supplemental Appropriations Act of 2026.
3 SECTION 2. This Act amends Act 250, Session Laws of Hawaii
4 2025, and other appropriations and authorizations effective
5 during fiscal biennium 2025-2027.
6 SECTION 3. Part I of Act 250, Session Laws of Hawaii 2025,
7 is amended by amending section 2 to read as follows:
8 "SECTION 2. DEFINITIONS. Unless otherwise clear from the
9 context, as used in this Act:
10 "Capital project number" means the official number of the
11 capital project, as assigned by the responsible organization.
12 "Expending agency" means the executive department,
13 independent commission, bureau, office, board, or other
14 establishment of the state government (other than the
15 legislature. Office of Hawaiian Affairs, and judiciary), the
16 political subdivisions of the State, or any quasi-public
17 institution supported in whole or in part by state funds, which
